{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Ellipse"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore7EllipseV","symbolKind":"method","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294","fileName":"RendererEffect.swift"}},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Ellipse\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed down to each subview.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/ellipse\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Ellipse/geometryGroup()":{"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/ellipse\/geometrygroup()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Ellipse\/geometryGroup()","title":"geometryGroup()"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Ellipse":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Ellipse"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Ellipse"}],"title":"Ellipse","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/ellipse","abstract":[{"text":"An ellipse aligned inside th